ck the &#8216;use with custom post types&#8217; checkbox and update the settings. It should then be turned on.<br />\nAdditionally, you can HIDE the option from specific post types if you need to. On the options page, in the section for &#8216;hide metabox for following post types&#8217;, check the boxes for any custom ...\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"dfischer\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:716:\"<p>Yes, you can.</p>\n<p>You need to turn it on (it should be on by default, unless you upgraded from an older version). Go into the plugin option and check the &#8216;use with custom post types&#8217; checkbox and update the settings. It should then be turned on.</p>\n<p>Additionally, you can HIDE the option from specific post types if you need to. On the options page, in the section for &#8216;hide metabox for following post types&#8217;, check the boxes for any custom post type you do not want the plugin to be used for. It will turn off the option box when adding a new item for that post type, and will not allow for hooking into any posts with the post type (Quick Redirects are the exception to that).</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:90:\"http://www.fischercreativemedia.com/faqs/can-i-use-the-plugin-with-custom-post-types/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s