 region\'s lack of dependence on Europe, for example, has shielded them from contagion - it does, however, mean that the region suffers when a large economy begins to slow or demnd begins to fall. Given their reliance on one another, flat demand in one country often has a knock-on effect on others. We saw weakening growth in China, for example, damaging trade growth in countries such as South Korea, Japan and Australia. However Delta expects a reasonable level of growth in total trade in Asia-Pacific in 2013 at 5.8%; we do not expect a dramatic drop in trade in China (7.4% total trade growth), indeed its economy may stabilise in 2013 as it ramps up its imports, thereby creating a strong foundation for growth in future.','Aisia Pacific','','publish','closed','open','','aisia-pacific','','','2013-08-16 16:58:51','2013-08-16 16:58:51','',0,'http://localhost/delta/?p=180',6,'post','',0),(181,1,'2013-08-16 14:41:41','2013-08-16 14:41:41','','Aisia Pacific','','inherit','closed','open','','180-revision-v1','','','2013-08-16 14:41:41','2013-08-16 14:41:41','',180,'http://localhost/delta/180-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(182,1,'2013-08-16 14:45:52','2013-08-16 14:45:52','Markets breathed a sigh of relief after China released better-than-expected trade data in early January. As the world\'s second-largest economy, China\'s economic fortunes are inextricably linked to those of the world and, indeed the Asia-Pacific. China ranks first for imports and exports to the Asia-Pacific and intra-regional tarde is paramount to their success; eight of Asia-Pacific\'s top-ten export partners are from within the region.\r\n\r\nIn some respects, this setup is beneficial - the region\'s lack of dependence on Europe, for example, has shielded them from contagion - it does, however, mean that the region suffers when a large economy begins to slow or demnd begins to fall. Given their reliance on one another, flat demand in one country often has a knock-on effect on others. We saw weakening